                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>Five connecting fragments of a white crystalline marble plaque, of which the right margin is damaged and the lower edge broken. Top, left and right edges are roughly finished. The rear is finished, but with a series of vertical grooves creating relief elements, with similarity to a triglyph. The marble has clearly been re-used from an earlier architectural element. The whole has been remounted on perspex.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.htm">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">22.8</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">28.4-29</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">2-2.6 (upper left to lower right)</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>Four lines of Latin letters approximately centred on the stone, but not perfectly horizontal. The first two lines are larger, with hedera in line 1, basic interpuncts elsewhere.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
